      "lesson title": "AI Transcription Tools in Healthcare Settings",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces healthcare professionals to the growing use of AI transcription tools in clinical environments, exploring how these technologies can support documentation and reduce administrative burden. You will examine the key privacy risks that arise when sensitive patient information is processed by automated systems, including concerns around data storage, consent, and third-party access. The lesson also covers accuracy limitations that can occur with AI transcription, such as mishearing medical terminology or misattributing speech, and why these errors can have serious consequences in a healthcare context. By the end of the lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to evaluate these tools critically and apply practical safeguards when using them in consultations and clinical note-taking. No prior technical knowledge is required, making this lesson suitable for anyone working in or alongside healthcare settings who wants to use AI transcription tools responsibly.",
